OFFICIAL OPENCODE PLUGIN DOCUMENTATION:

Plugin Registration Methods:
1. Local: .opencode/plugins/ (project) or ~/.config/opencode/plugins/ (global)
2. npm: Add to opencode.json plugin array

Available Hooks:
- command.executed
- file.edited, file.watcher.updated
- message.updated, message.part.updated
- session.created, session.compacted, session.idle
- tool.execute.before, tool.execute.after
- permission.replied

Plugin Structure:
```typescript
import { Plugin, tool } from '@opencode-ai/plugin'

export const LinePlugin: Plugin = async (ctx) => {
  return {
    tool: {
      'line-status': tool({
        description: 'Show line-cook workflow status',
        args: {},
        async execute(args, context) {
          // implementation
        },
      }),
    },
    event: {
      'session.created': async (event) => {
        // auto-prime on session start
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Sources:
- https://opencode.ai/docs/plugins/
- https://opencode.ai/docs/custom-tools/
